OTP, Mol Boost Hungary’s BUX Index, Forint Rises for Fourth Day

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-10-10T07:06:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/otp-mol-boost-hungary-s-bux-index-forint-rises-for-fourth-day.html
The Hungarian forint strengthened
for a fourth day against the euro while stocks rose.  The forint gained 0.5 percent to 295.4 per euro at 9:04
a.m. in Budapest. OTP Bank Nyrt.,  Hungary ’s largest lender, rose
0.8 percent to 3,180 forint. Mol Nyrt., the country’s largest
refiner, rose 1.3 percent to 16,000 forint. The benchmark BUX
index rose 0.8 percent to 16,415.79.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  